  <div data-component="article-content">


            <p>Even though <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/gta-6-developer-rockstar-games-hacked-once-again-but-insists-only-a-limited-amount-of-non-material-company-information-was-compromised">the hacker group ShinyHunters successfully broke through (part of) Rockstar Games' security</a> and extracted internal data, the developer and its huge publisher, Take-Two, haven't minded the unfortunate event much. In fact, it seems they're coming out on top.</p>
<p>Earlier this week, we learned <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/gta-online-daily-revenue-data-and-more-leaks">GTA Online was still making Rockstar around $1.3m per day</a>, with annual estimates hitting nearly $500m from microtransactions alone. For an online mode which has been around for over a decade now, it's stunning data and the kind of lasting, constant revenue many big-name publishers can only dream of.</p> <figure>
<p>
<a aria-label="GTA 6 (Grand Theft Auto 6) - Official Trailer 2" data-platform="youtube" href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/sQEGy86F2gE?autoplay=1" onclick="((e) => { e.preventDefault(); e.currentTarget.closest('.video_wrapper').innerHTML = e.currentTarget.querySelector('template').innerHTML; enableElements(); })(event)" title="Click to play video from YouTube">
