</p>
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sQEGy86F2gE" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Watch on YouTube</a></figure>
<p>Unsurprisingly, shareholders like this information. Take-Two's stock has shot up since yesterday (hat tip to <a href="https://www.videogameschronicle.com/news/rockstar-hackers-actually-made-take-twos-stock-increase-after-leaking-how-much-gta-online-is-making/">VGC</a>), confirming an upward trend since Rockstar came out to say the security breach wasn't a big deal. For reference, <a href="https://www.google.com/finance/quote/TTWO:NASDAQ?window=5D">the stock</a> was valued at $195,12 last Friday. It's now sitting at $205,10, up from $202,26 when the market opened yesterday. The biggest jump happened over 30 minutes early in the morning EU time.</p>
<p>Nothing is known about the (likely) next iteration of <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/gta-online">GTA Online</a> yet, but considering the games industry is still waiting for more details on <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/grand-theft-auto-vi">Grand Theft Auto 6</a>'s 19th November release, it might be a while before the powers that be are ready to unveil what the next multiplayer GTA looks like.</p><p>Meanwhile, Take-Two boss Strauss Zelnick <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/gta-6-couldnt-be-made-by-ai-suggests-take-two-boss-there-is-no-creativity-that-can-exist-by-definition-in-any-ai-model">recently commented on the current AI craze</a> and stated "no creativity... can exist by definition in any AI model." Moreover, after some internal work done around AI tools, <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/take-two-lays-off-ai-team">the company has just laid off its entire AI team</a>.</p>

